          "id": "medquad-chunk-48e013a736f03a91",
          "title": "What are the treatments for Brain and Spinal Tumors ?",
          "content": "The most common treatments for brain and spinal tumors include surgery, radiation therapy, and chemotherapy. These approaches aim to remove or shrink the tumor and alleviate symptoms. In some cases, doctors may also prescribe steroids to help reduce swelling in the brain or spinal cord caused by the tumor. Each treatment plan is tailored to the individual based on the type of tumor, its location, and the patient's overall health.\nContext recap: The most common treatments for brain and spinal tumors include surgery, radiation therapy, and chemotherapy. These approaches aim to remove or shrink the tumor and alleviate symptoms. In some cases, doctors may also prescribe steroids to help reduce swelling in the brain or spinal cord caused by the tumor. Each treatment plan is tailored to the individual based on the type of tumor, its location, and the patient's overall health.\nContext recap: The most common treatments for brain and spinal tumors include surgery, radiation therapy, and chemotherapy. These approaches aim to remove or shrink the tumor and alleviate symptoms. In some cases, doctors may also prescribe steroids to help reduce swelling in the brain or spinal cord caused by the tumor. Each treatment plan is tailored to the individual based on the type of tumor, its location, and the patient's overall health.\nWhy this matters: What are the treatments for Brain and Spinal Tumors ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Neurology (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.\nContext recap: The most common treatments for brain and spinal tumors include surgery, radiation therapy, and chemotherapy. These approaches aim to remove or shrink the tumor and alleviate symptoms. In some cases, doctors may also prescribe steroids to help reduce swelling in the brain or spinal cord caused by the tumor. Each treatment plan is tailored to the individual based on the type of tumor, its location, and the patient's overall health.\nWhy this matters: What are the treatments for Brain and Spinal Tumors ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Neurology (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.",
          "kind": "concept"
